div.p:
The State Department reports that the following specific problems are holding up
                    progress in the negotiations: 

—[1 line not declassified];

—disagreement over cost estimates for construction by the U.S. of
                            Greek communication facilities;

—Greek insistence on limiting U.S. air operations at Hellenikon;
                            and

—a Greek reversal concerning a U.S. proposed periodic review provision
                            for the use of Souda Bay.
